# Download process (ropegeo-common)

Download orchestration lives in **`src/download/`** and is published as **`ropegeo-common/download`**. Common owns job planning, phases, tasks, and persistence types. **Mobile** (Phase 3) implements `DownloadPlatformHarness` — Expo FileSystem, Mapbox, AsyncStorage — in `Mobile/lib/download/`. Do **not** re-export Common download symbols from Mobile.

Shared download types live in **`src/download/types.ts`**. Types used by only one class stay in that class's file (e.g. private `TileListPage` in `FetchRopeGeoTileListTask`).

Custom download errors live in **`src/download/errors.ts`**.

Helper functions and registries live in **`src/download/helpers/`** (one module per file: constants, phase titles, planning, seeding, hydration registries, pending file transfer).

See also **document-package-exports.mdc** when adding README table rows for new public exports.

## Architecture

```
DownloadJobQueue → DownloadJob → DownloadPhase → DownloadTask (concrete)
                      ↑
         OnlinePageView.toDownloadJob()     (explore — full plan at enqueue)
         OnlinePagePreview.toDownloadJob()  (saved — delete + fetch JSON, then append)
```

| Type | Role |
| --- | --- |
| `DownloadJobQueue` | FIFO orchestration, persist/restore, foreground + BG ticks |
| `DownloadJob` | Mutable `phases[]`, `taskDependencies`, `runTick`, `appendPhases` |
| `DownloadPhase` | Parallel `tasks`, `title`, `progressPercent` |
| `DownloadTask` | One unit of work per tick; `dependencyKeys` (one or more) |
| `DownloadTaskDependency` | Per-consumer payload; `toStoredState` / `fromStoredState` |
| `DownloadPlatformHarness` | Common type; Mobile implements file/Mapbox/store I/O |
| `DownloadJobQueueStoredState` | Persisted queue envelope |
| `DownloadJobStoredState` | Persisted single job |
| `DownloadJobUISnapshot` | Runtime UI progress (not persisted) |

**Phase 1 is always** `[DeleteStoredPageTask]` on both explore and preview paths.

## Job entry points

- **Explore** — `OnlineRopewikiPageView.toDownloadJob(config)`: `buildDeleteStoredPagePhase()` + `planDownloadPhases(view)`. No `FetchPageJsonTask`.
- **Saved screen** — `OnlinePagePreview.toDownloadJob(config)`: delete phase + `FetchPageJsonTask` phase only at enqueue. `FetchPageJsonTask` calls `appendPhases(planDownloadPhases(view))` after page JSON is fetched.

## Dependencies

- Each dependency **key** is consumed by **exactly one** task.
- A task may consume **multiple keys** (e.g. `SaveOfflinePageTask` reads `saveOfflinePageView`, optional `saveOfflinePageImages`, `saveOfflinePageMiniMap`).
- **No merge helpers** — upstream tasks call `ctx.setDependency(key, dep)` for each downstream consumer key.

Keys live in `dependencies/downloadDependencyKeys.ts`. Register parsers in `helpers/downloadDependencyRegistry.ts`.

## Adding or updating a DownloadTask

1. Add `*TaskDependency` class + key in `downloadDependencyKeys.ts`.
2. Register `dependencyKind` in `helpers/downloadDependencyRegistry.ts`.
3. Subclass `DownloadTask`; set `dependencyKeys`; implement `runTick`, `toStoredState`, `fromStoredState`.
4. In `runTick`: `requireAllDependencies(ctx)` before work; on completion `ctx.setDependency()` for each produced key.
5. Wire into `planDownloadPhases()` + `seedConsumerDependencies()`. Preview jobs: only `FetchPageJsonTask` at build time; others appear after JSON fetch.
6. Register `taskKind` in `helpers/downloadTaskRegistry.ts`.
7. Add Jest coverage under `test/download/tasks/`; job-plan tests in `test/download/jobs/`.

## Coding guidelines

**Use `toDownloadJob()` on models — not standalone factory modules**

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
const job = view.toDownloadJob(config);

// ❌ BAD
const job = buildDownloadJobFromView(view, config);
```

**Use `fromStoredState` for persistence — not `fromResult`**

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
DownloadJob.fromStoredState(raw);

// ❌ BAD
DownloadJob.fromResult(apiBody);
```

**Cap parallel HTTP / file work per tick**

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
for (const batch of chunk(pending, LIST_HTTP_BATCH_SIZE)) {
  await Promise.all(batch.map((item) => enqueueOrReconcile(item, platformHarness)));
}

// ❌ BAD
await Promise.all(pending.map((item) => enqueueOrReconcile(item, platformHarness)));
```

List tasks use `LIST_HTTP_BATCH_SIZE`; file tasks use `pendingFileTransfer` reconcile + enqueue batches (`TILE_FILE_BATCH_SIZE`).

## Phase titles

`titleForPhase(tasks)` in `helpers/downloadPhaseTitles.ts`:

| Condition | Title |
| --- | --- |
| Single `DeleteStoredPageTask` | Deleting stored page |
| Single `FetchPageJsonTask` | Downloading page |
| Contains `FetchImageFilesTask` with `total > 0` | Downloading Media |
| Contains `FetchRegionRouteListTask` | Downloading local routes |
| Contains `FetchMapboxPackTask` | Downloading Mapbox Pack |
| Contains `FetchRopeGeoTileFilesTask` | Downloading map data |
| Contains `SaveOfflinePageTask` | Saving page |

## Tests

- **Explore path** — `test/download/jobs/ropewikiPageView.test.ts`: all `planDownloadPhases` / `toDownloadJob` variations; phase 1 always delete; no `FetchPageJsonTask`.
- **Preview path** — `test/download/jobs/ropewikiPagePreview.test.ts`: initial 2 phases; mock `httpRequest`; assert `appendPhases` matches explore plan; stored-state round-trip.
- Do **not** put download job planning tests under `test/models/pageViews/`.

## Package export

Add public symbols to `src/download/index.ts` and a matching row in **README.md** (`ropegeo-common/download`). Do **not** re-export download from `src/models/index.ts`.
